divs: Sighting DetailsSighted an object at about 35 degrees elevation, above the constellation Scorpio. The object appeared in the east and moved to the ENE. Lost to sight at about 20 elevation after about 20 seconds. Very faint, white and star-like, and moving very fast. No anti-collision or strobe lights observed, and no sound. No other aircraft observed at the time of the sighting.
Summary: Sighted an object at about 35 degrees elevation, above the constellation Scorpio.
